cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection in images, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper introduces a new loss function for training object detection models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of this loss function in 3D vehicle detection, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves the use of a parameter that is automatically adapted during training, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
